  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Select Medical?",
  "response": "Congratulations on the new job! Here's a breakdown of what new employees at Select Medical should be aware of on their first day, covering key areas:\n\n**Before Your First Day:**\n\n*   **Confirmation:** Ensure you have clear instructions regarding your start time, location, who to report to, and any necessary paperwork to bring.\n*   **Dress Code:** Confirm the dress code (business casual is generally a safe bet unless otherwise specified for your role/location).\n*   **Map It Out:** Plan your route to the location and factor in potential traffic delays.  Consider parking arrangements.\n*   **Review Materials:** If you received any onboarding materials beforehand, review them.\n\n**On Your First Day:**\n\n**1. Paperwork and Administrative Tasks:**\n\n*   **Expect initial HR paperwork:** Be prepared to complete forms related to benefits, taxes, payroll, emergency contacts, and compliance.\n*   **I-9 Verification:** You will need to provide documentation to verify your identity and authorization to work in the U.S. (e.g., driver's license, social security card, passport).\n*   **Company Policies:** Pay attention to the review of company policies and procedures (HR, safety, compliance).  Don't hesitate to ask questions.\n*   **System Setup:** You will likely be setting up your login credentials for various company systems (email, HR platform, etc.).\n\n**2. Introductions and Orientation:**\n\n*   **Team Introductions:** Your supervisor will likely introduce you to your immediate team members and potentially other relevant colleagues. Be polite, friendly, and remember names.\n*   **Company Overview:** You'll receive an overview of Select Medical's mission, values, services, and organizational structure. Understand how your role fits into the bigger picture.\n*   **Facility Tour:** Expect a tour of your work area and key areas within the facility (break room, restrooms, etc.).\n*   **Mentorship/Buddy System:** Some Select Medical locations have mentorship or buddy programs for new hires. Take advantage of this opportunity for guidance.\n\n**3. Role-Specific Training and Expectations:**\n\n*   **Job Description Review:** Your supervisor should review your job description, responsibilities, and performance expectations.\n*   **Training Schedule:** You'll likely receive a training schedule outlining the onboarding process.\n*   **Software/Equipment Training:** Depending on your role, you'll receive training on relevant software, equipment, and systems.\n*   **Performance Goals:** Discuss initial goals and how your performance will be measured.\n*   **Ask Questions!** This is the time to clarify any uncertainties about your role, responsibilities, or expectations.\n\n**4. Company Culture and Values:**\n\n*   **Focus on Patient Care:** Understand that Select Medical prioritizes quality patient care.\n*   **Teamwork and Collaboration:** Emphasize teamwork and collaboration with colleagues.\n*   **Respect and Communication:** Demonstrate respect for patients, families, and colleagues.\n*   **Professionalism:** Maintain a professional demeanor and adhere to company policies.\n*   **Compliance:** Adhere to all compliance regulations related to healthcare.\n\n**5. General Tips for a Successful First Day:**\n\n*   **Be Punctual:** Arrive on time.\n*   **Be Proactive:** Take initiative and ask questions.\n*   **Be Positive:** Show enthusiasm and a willingness to learn.\n*   **Be Respectful:** Treat everyone with respect and courtesy.\n*   **Take Notes:** Jot down important information to help you remember it.\n*   **Observe and Listen:** Pay attention to the environment and how things are done.\n*   **Be Patient:** It takes time to learn a new job and company culture.\n*   **Find a Familiar Face:** If you know anyone else working at Select Medical, reach out to them.\n*   **Don't Be Afraid to Ask for Help:** If you're struggling with something, don't hesitate to ask for assistance.\n\n**Specifically for Select Medical:**\n\n*   **Focus on Select Medical's Mission:** Select Medical's mission is to provide exceptional patient care and improve the lives of those they serve. Familiarize yourself with their commitment to rehabilitation, critical illness recovery, and outpatient care.\n*   **Understand the Different Divisions:** Select Medical operates various divisions (hospitals, rehabilitation centers, outpatient clinics). Be aware of the specific focus of your division.\n*   **Emphasis on Safety:** Healthcare environments have strict safety protocols. Pay close attention to safety training and procedures.\n*   **Electronic Health Records (EHR):** Training on the specific EHR system used at your location will be important.\n*   **Compliance with Regulations:** Select Medical is subject to strict regulations (HIPAA, etc.). Be sure to understand and comply with all applicable regulations.\n\n**Questions to Ask (if not covered):**\n\n*   What are the expectations for the first week/month?\n*   What are the best ways to communicate with my team/supervisor?\n*   Who should I contact if I have questions about [specific area]?\n*   What are the key performance indicators (KPIs) for my role?\n*   What opportunities are there for professional development and training?\n\nBy preparing for your first day and actively engaging in the onboarding process, you can set yourself up for a successful start at Select Medical. Good luck!\n",
